You are working on CTO Map — a 52-week Technical CTO Mastery curriculum tracker.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router, NOT Pages Router)
- TypeScript (strict)
- Prisma ORM with SQLite (schema at prisma/schema.prisma)
- Tailwind CSS with dark mode (darkMode: "class")
- Zod for validation (lib/validators.ts)
- dnd-kit for drag-and-drop
- Jest + fast-check for testing

## Critical Rules
1. ALL UI must have dark mode: every `text-gray-900` needs `dark:text-gray-100`, every `bg-white` needs `dark:bg-gray-900`
2. ALL interactive elements need `min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px]` for touch targets
3. Use `'use client';` for components with hooks/state/events
4. Use existing contexts: `useToast()`, `useProgress()`, `useTheme()` from lib/
5. After modifying TaskItems → run `calculateDayCompletion()` → update Day
6. After modifying Day completion → check if Week should auto-complete
7. Use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps` (React 19 + Next 14 peer dep conflict)
8. API responses: `/api/task-items` returns `{ learn: [], build: [] }` NOT a flat array

## File Structure
- Pages: app/[route]/page.tsx
- API: app/api/[endpoint]/route.ts
- Components: components/[Name].tsx
- Utils: lib/[name].ts
- Tests: __tests__/[name].test.ts
- Types: lib/types.ts (all shared interfaces)

## Common Patterns
- Toast: `const { showToast } = useToast(); showToast("msg", "success");`
- Progress: `const { refreshProgress } = useProgress();` — call after completion changes
- Optimistic updates: update UI first, revert on API failure
- Use `useRef` for callback props to avoid infinite loops in useEffect deps

## Database
- 3 Phases → 52 Weeks → 312 Days → N TaskItems
- Completion cascade: TaskItems → Day → Week (automatic)
- Key constraint: Day has @@unique([weekId, sortOrder])
